    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> panko breadcrumbs </strong>and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 6-8 min or until golden, stirring frequently</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
